cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on designing a conversational avatar and analyzing dialogues collected from conversations with older adults. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of LISSA, an on-screen virtual agent, to improve users' communication skills. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper describes the automatic spoken dialogue manager for LISSA. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with spoken dialogue and feedback on non-verbal behavior. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a less likely category, but could be relevant as the paper discusses the use of an on-screen virtual agent.
